text.section:
The provisions of any local law or ordinance adopted under this section shall not apply to the following transfers of a residential rental facility:
A transfer as a result of a foreclosure made under the terms of a mortgage or deed of trust;
A transfer to a mortgagee in lieu of foreclosure or a transfer under other proceedings, arrangement or deed in lieu of foreclosure;
A transfer made under a judicial sale or other judicial proceeding brought to secure payment of a debt or for the purpose of securing the performance of an obligation;
A transfer of the interest of one co-tenant to another co-tenant by operation of law or otherwise;
A transfer made by will or descent or by intestate distribution;
A transfer made to a municipal or county government, to the State government, or to an agency, instrumentality, or political subdivision of government;
A transfer to a spouse, son, or daughter;
A transfer made under the liquidation of a partnership or corporation; or
A transfer into a partnership or corporation wholly owned by the person(s) so contributing.
